{
  "text": "Appendix 2. Indexation (A) To Trend Inflation [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] assume that the new price set in a generic period t is actually indexed to trend inflation. Hence, even if the firm is not allowed to revise its price, the latter grows at the same rate as trend inflation. Then the problem of the firm is",
  "correct_citation": {
